## Eco Score Ranges (realistic values from Serve360 reports)
- Energy: 30–65 kWh/room-night (industry avg ~50; good hotels ~35)
- Water: 120–280 L/room-night (industry avg ~200; good hotels ~140)
- Waste diversion: 35–85% (industry avg ~55%; certified hotels ~75%)
- Certifications: LEED Silver, LEED Gold, Green Key, EarthCheck
- F&B sourcing score: 5–9 (based on local/organic sourcing %)

## Loading Pattern (Backend)
```python
# app/data/loader.py
import json
from pathlib import Path

SEEDS_PATH = Path(__file__).parent.parent.parent / "data" / "seeds"

def load_seed(filename: str) -> dict | list:
    with open(SEEDS_PATH / filename) as f:
        return json.load(f)

# Loaded once at startup into module-level dicts:
HOTELS: dict[str, dict] = {h["id"]: h for h in load_seed("hotels.json")}
GUESTS: dict[str, dict] = {g["id"]: g for g in load_seed("guests.json")}
STAYS: dict[str, dict] = {s["id"]: s for s in load_seed("stays.json")}
```
